transcript_text: So I don't know if this is actually this guy asking for help, but this is a pretty common situation  and I feel like others could benefit from this. First of all, I would drop the weight in the compounds  and try to prioritize, perfecting and improving your form. The next thing I would say is focus  on strengthening your hips. Do more unilateral exercises such as single leg deadlifts or  Bulgarian split squats. All of your power on a squat and a deadlift comes from your hips,  and typically when people complain about having a week back with their squats,  it's not their back, it's actually their hips being weak and their back just can't compensate.
